    <subfield code="y">00000 Plots of the scalar potentials, $V(\Phi)$, as a function of the dimensionless scalar field, $\Phi \equiv \sqrt{\frac{6 \pi}{m^2_{Pl}}}\,(\phi - \phi_0)$. The solid line represents the scalar potential, expressed by Eq. (\ref{V2Ch}) for the value $\alpha=0.2$. The dot-dashed line represents the same potential, but for the value $\alpha = 0.8$. The scalar potential $V(\Phi)$ is expressed as a multiple of the constant $\displaystyle V_0\equiv \frac{1}{2}B^{\frac{1}{1+\alpha}}$.</subfield>
